nodes.text: Corellian sap-wine was a type of wine from the planet Corellia. It was potable by humans and possessed alcoholic properties. Several months after the Battle of Endor, which occurred in 4 ABY, former Imperial loyalty officer Sinjir Rath Velus consumed Corellian sap-wine and became drunk. His crewmate Temmin Wexley tried to ask him for advice concerning self-identity, but upon attempting to respond, Velus burped and passed out.
Corellian sap-wine was first mentioned in Aftermath: Life Debt, a 2016 canon novel written by Chuck Wendig.
